name: diesel-electric generating set production 18.5kW | diesel-electric generating set, 18.5kW | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/12406/documentation

This dataset represents rough estimation of the production of diesel-electric generating set which can be attached to a reefer (refrigerated intermodal shipping container) and supply the power needed for maintaining the atmosphere inside the reefer.;This type of generator set (called often genset) is produced by many differnt producers. This dataset is build based on technical information available on following two types of genset; Carrier RG15 and Thermo King SGCO-3000.;Generator Set Unit for reefer, technical description (Carrier, 2014, Operation and service for 69RG15 generator set units, http://dms.hvacpartners.com//docs/2000/Public/04/T-361.pdf, accessed 20141218).;Generator Set Unit clipped on a reefer (http://www.mouzaliotis.com/portal/index.php/containers/reefer-containers, accessed 20141218).

The activity starts when all the individual parts are brought to the production site for assembling. 

The activity ends when the generator set unit is assembled.
